<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-518-350  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 518 350.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  June 4 1990 v7 n22 p24(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>TurboPrint upgrade features enhanced font-handling ability.andO;(printer controller from Gradco Systems Inc.)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Gradco Systems Inc. (product enhancement).andO;Product:   Gradco Printer Systems TurboPrint (Peripheral controller) (productenhancement).andO;Topic:     ControllersPrintersEnhancementsFonts.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Gradco Printer Systems recently announced an upgraded version of itsTurboPrint printer controller that boasts enhanced font-handling capabilitiesand improved printer support, officials said.andM;The new TurboPrint controller, available for $1,195, fits into AT compatiblesand features 2.5M bytes of memory and a 32-bit microprocessor.andP;  Thecontroller boosts the print speed of Hewlett-Packard Co.'s LaserJet printersby as much as 50 percent, said Gradco officials in Irvine, Calif.andM;The controller also works with printers from Canon U.S.A.andP;  Inc. and BrotherInternational Inc., they said.andM;To enhance desktop-publishing output, Gradco equipped the new version with 35scalable outline fonts.andP;  The fonts can be used with the software packagessupported by the current TurboPrint controller, including WordPerfect,PageMaker and Ventura Publisher, officials said.andM;Current TurboPrint users can upgrade their cards for an additional fee, whichGradco has not yet set.andM;Gradco can be contacted at (800) 628-1538.andO;</TEXT></DOC>